jose blandon a former top adviser to the panamanian government 
who used to make official trips to cuba on behalf of gen manuel 
antonio noriega told congress in february 1988 that castro sees 
narcotics smuggling as element of a broader antiamerican strategy 
blandon said us military involvement in central america gave 
castro the moral justification to do anything against the united 
states anything that was necessary 
