america the rutherford institute the freedom council and the 
american family association falwell said 
much of the political agenda of the religious right including 
making abortion illegal allowing tuition tax credits for private 
schools and silent prayer in public schools remains unfulfilled 
but falwell credited the moral majority with registering 
millions of voters and leading religious conservatives in 
electing ronald reagan defeating a dozen liberal us senators in 
1980 reelecting reagan in 1984 and electing bush last year 
he said the organization also helped place conservative judges 
throughout the federal courts and successfully lobbied for 
legislation such as the equal access bill which permits studentrun 
religious groups to meet in public schools 
