today that bars the state from enforcing its yearold obscenity law 
saying it is unconstitutionally vague and unfairly exempts libraries 
and schools 
under the ruling by us district judge jp stadtmueller the 
state may appeal to the federal appeals court or ask for a trial if 
the state does neither the preliminary injunction would become 
permanent and the law would have to be scrapped 
two milwaukee stores denmark book store and paradise video 
store in addition to pure pleasure ii bookstore in oshkosh filed 
suit in federal court against the state calling the obscenity 
statute unconstitutional 
since the law was passed last spring no one has been criminally 
prosecuted the law which was intended to halt commercial traffic 
in hardcore pornography calls for jail terms of up to five years 
and fines of up to 10000 for pornography wholesalers 
under the statute material is obscene if it lacks serious 
literary artistic political educational or scientific value 
attorney general donald j hanaway said today that he had not 
seen the decision and would not comment yet 
