in his decision stadtmueller said the statute was 
unconstitutionally vague the judge said it was difficult to 
determine whether the law was violated by depicting sexually 
explicit conduct by describing sexually explicit conduct or both 
in addition stadtmueller said the state violated the equal 
protection clause of the constitution by exempting libraries 
schools and universities from prosecution under the statute 
the law allows a school library to commercially distribute 
obscene materials without the threat of prosecution but does not 
allow an adult bookstore to do the same the judge said 
the judge also found unconstitutional the laws distinction 
between contract printers and bookstore clerks under the statute 
the printers would not be threatened with prosecution but the store 
clerks would 
stadtmueller did rule in favor of the state however when he 
said that the legislature intended to include videotapes as well as 
film under the statute 
