in the sport of parliamentary discourse such exchanges are 
shouted above a din of wisecracks jeering or a drone of hear 
hear 
speaker of the house bernard weatherill has to bellow order 
order when the right honorable members are particularly frisky 
in the event of an occasion of grave disorder television 
cameras will be obliged to zero in on weatherill not the ruckus in 
the benches 
if the speaker is receiving advice from a lowly clerk the rules 
adopted monday require the camera turn away 
otherwise the lens may gaze at the head and shoulders of the 
legislator speaking although a reaction shot is permitted if 
another member is mentioned by name 
john wakeham leader of the house of commons and chairman of the 
select committee on televising its proceedings said the rules will 
produce an electronic hansard a video equivalent of the 
official printed record 
the 9month experiment begins in november when queen elizabeth ii 
presides at the state opening of parliament the following july the 
house will debate whether to permit permanent coverage 
the british broadcasting corp and independent television news 
have protested the restrictions 
the range of camera shots being proposed is so restricted 
especially during questions and statements and during what the 
report describes as periods of disorder that what the viewers will 
be seeing may well be less than full balanced fair and accurate 
said itn associate editor glyn mathias 
there will be a burden on the commentator to explain to viewers 
what they cannot see for themselves he added 
an amendment to permit unrestricted coverage was defeated on a 
vote of 27498 
matthew parris author of the commons sketch in the times of 
london ridiculed the rules last month 
readers at any given moment the least interesting thing in 
