the new satellite is the second advanced model navstar to be 
launched it is designed to tell us and allied military forces 
where they are within 50 feet anywhere in the world on land sea 
or in the air and in any weather 
ground stations tracked the satellite for nearly two days to 
accurately determine its orbital path then sent a radio signal at 
312 pm monday to start the motor on the new path the 
satellites high and low points are both at about 11000 miles 
the burn was succesful and everything looks good said lt 
johnn kennedy a spokesman for the air force space division in los 
angeles 
officials said ground controllers would check out the payloads 
systems for between 35 and 40 days before placing it on operational 
patrol joining eight other navstar satellites already in orbit 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

