agree that children need fat for growth about 30 to 40 percent of a 
childs calories should come from fat recommends the american 
academy of pediatrics thats close to the 3439 percent spread 
shown in a federal survey of the current diets of american children 
i think runofthemill parents should be aware that a highfat 
diet is not good advises the academys nutrition committee 
