parts and falsified test results on critical components of air force 
cruise missles and navy av8b harrier jets 
ms oharenko said the local investigation is not related to that 
criminal indictment 
the defense systems division which makes radarjamming equipment 
for military aircraft employs about 4000 people at its 
headquarters in rolling meadows and two other facilities in nearby 
arlington heights and elk grove village 
the division produces systems to shield b52 and b1b bombers and 
f15 fighter jets from detection by enemy radar it has suffered 
from cutbacks in military spending and over the past year and has 
reduced its work force by more than 1000 people through layoffs and 
attrition 
